quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to remove all siblings of the element with id="txt".
[!raw!]
$("{0}txt").{1}().{2}();

Fill in the blanks to empty the second child element of the element with id="nav".
[!raw!]
var e = $("{0}").{1}();
e.eq({2}).{3}();

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Removing Content[/h1]

The [b]empty()[/b] method is used to remove the child elements of the selected element(s). For example:
[b]HTML[/b]: [code format="html" ]<div>
   <p style="color:red">Red</p>
   <p style="color:green">Green</p>
   <p style="color:blue">Blue</p>
</div>[/code]
[b]CSS: [code format="css" ]div {
  background-color: aqua;
  width: 300px;
  height: 200px;
}[/code]
JS[/b]:[code format="js" codeId="1125"]$("div").[b]empty[/b]();[/code]
[note]This removes all the three child elements of the div, leaving it empty.[/note]
